<dl id="n09087b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09087b">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09087b"> 87(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Melanesian / chow</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Reviews.</b> / Isles of Illusion. Anonymous; with a foreword and Edited by Bohun Lynch. (London: Constable & Co.) &hellip; the anonymous writer of the letters which make up Isles of Illusion is by no means a fresh soul.&hellip; Add to this that he is an Oxford man for whom the <mark>Melanesians</mark> are &ldquo;niggers&rdquo; and for whom the imported Chinese are &ldquo;<mark>Chows</mark>,&rdquo; and you will perceive that he has many cycles to go through before he becomes a fresh soul.&hellip; <small> <a name="IS1mar24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IS1mar24"><cite title="source">Irish Statesman</cite></a> (1 March 1924) 788f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
